  <li><details><summary>JavaScript Embeded</summary>

      <h3 style="color: black;">Javascript Embed</h3>
       <p style="color: black">In this method javaScript functions are defined in the page by using the &ltscript&gt <br>
        So that they are accessible to any element within the page</p>
      <html>
      <title>JavaScript Embed</title>
      <script type="text/javascript">
        <!--
        function printPage() {
          window.print();
        }
        -->
      </script>
      <body>
      <form style="color:black;">
        <h4>Click print to Print content in the page</h4>
        --><input type="button" value="print" onclick="printPage();">
      </form>
      </body>
      </html>
      <p style="color: black">A client side script is defined by using its MIME type or language. A MIME type will give access
        to various file extensions.The JavaScript MIME type is "text/javascript"</p>
      <h4 style="color: black">Target JavaScript towards Old Version browsers:</h4>
      <p style="color: black">The JavaScript functions must be enclosed in HTML comments in order to target any old version browsers.</p>
      <pre style="color: black">
    &ltscript type="text/javascript"&gt
      &lt!--
      function PrintPage() {
        window.print();
      }
      --&gt
    &lt/script&gt
  </pre><br></details></li>
